On startup the following warning can be seen in the logs:
{code}
2016-04-27T04:13:31.086329+00:00 node163 crowd: 2016-04-27 04:13:31,086 http-nio-127.0.0.1-8081-exec-9 WARN [common.security.jersey.XsrfResourceFilterFactory] Detected usage of the com.atlassian.annotations.security.XsrfProtectionExcluded annotation loaded from elsewhere. com.atlassian.plugins.rest.atlassian-rest-module [29] != WebappClassLoader{code}

This is informational, and doesn't affect functionality. Probably caused by the rest plugin getting it's copy of atlassian-annotations dependency from core rather than from atlassian-rest-module.

There is a typo in whatever component generates this line of the {{<Crowd Home Directory>/logs/atlassian-crowd.log}} on startup:



{noformat}
2016-04-26 15:21:00,739 localhost-startStop-1 INFO [crowd.console.listener.StartupListener] License is valid. Support Entitlemenet Number (SEN) is SEN-XXXXXXX
{noformat}


Entitlement is spelled incorrectly :)

About the most trivial bug possible!

